alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 13 at 7:26PM PST until January 14 at 8:40AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. .The Snoqualmie River will continue to recede. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH FRIDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Carnation. * WHEN...Until tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 54.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will flood much of the farm land and several roads from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:15 PM PST Thursday the stage was 54.4 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:15 PM PST Thursday was 56.8 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage this evening and continue falling to 48.1 feet Sunday afternoon. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 54.4 feet on 10/26/1945. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by late tonight at 530 AM PST.
